WEBVTT

00:02.500 --> 00:04.500
Danny was a scholar, you know?

00:04.510 --> 00:08.440
He was studying for his PHD
in physics.

00:08.440 --> 00:10.610
He had a big future, Mr. stone.

00:11.380 --> 00:13.410
- I know how painful
this must be.

00:13.520 --> 00:16.780
- He had dinner with us
every Sunday night.

00:16.790 --> 00:18.820
The night that he was killed...

00:18.820 --> 00:20.520
- they know all this, honey.

00:20.520 --> 00:22.520
- We usually walked him
to the bus stop.

00:22.530 --> 00:24.690
That night...

00:24.690 --> 00:28.960
I was too tired,
and you had to watch your game.

00:34.540 --> 00:36.840
- Mr. and Mrs. Nasiri,

00:36.840 --> 00:38.740
I'm so sorry about Danny.

00:38.740 --> 00:42.210
- Damn, dude. I just wanted
to tell you I didn't kill him.

00:42.210 --> 00:45.480
- Byron, come on. Let's go.

00:45.480 --> 00:48.780
- Danny didn't do anything
to that boy.

00:48.790 --> 00:50.690
- Except look different.

00:50.690 --> 00:52.950
- I assure you:
Most Americans will not tolerate

00:52.960 --> 00:54.860
the murder of an innocent boy.

00:54.860 --> 00:56.760
- We should go.

01:00.930 --> 01:03.630
- Monday morning,
around 1:45 A.M.,

01:03.630 --> 01:05.600
we found the body
in an abandoned building.

01:05.600 --> 01:08.770
He was already deceased
when we arrived.

01:08.770 --> 01:10.540
- You didn't just happen
by the building, I assume.

01:10.540 --> 01:12.970
- It isn't counsel's place
to assume facts not in evidence.

01:12.980 --> 01:14.840
- Rephrase:
Did you merely happen by

01:14.840 --> 01:15.910
the building on south...

01:15.910 --> 01:17.550
- counsel is leading
the witness.

01:17.550 --> 01:18.850
- And counsel forgets
this is a preliminary hearing,

01:18.850 --> 01:22.080
Rephrase: What brought you
to that abandoned building.

01:22.090 --> 01:26.650
- An anonymous call
from what we later learned was

01:26.660 --> 01:28.720
a tweaker who was squatting
in the building.

01:28.730 --> 01:30.530
- What condition
was Danny Nasiri in

01:30.530 --> 01:31.560
when you found him?

01:31.560 --> 01:34.730
He had been beaten to death
with a tire iron

01:34.730 --> 01:37.000
that we found
in an adjacent dumpster.

01:37.000 --> 01:39.030
- Is this how you found
Danny Nasiri?

01:39.040 --> 01:41.940
- It is.

01:41.940 --> 01:44.640
- And this?
- Yep.

01:44.640 --> 01:46.740
- What initially led you
to suspect the defendant,

01:46.740 --> 01:47.740
Byron Welch?

01:47.740 --> 01:49.080
- We learned from campus police

01:49.080 --> 01:50.780
there had been
a prior altercation

01:50.780 --> 01:52.750
between him and Danny Nasiri.

01:52.750 --> 01:55.620
- And why did you eventually
arrest Byron Welch?

01:55.620 --> 01:57.690
- We found a sweatshirt
that was stained

01:57.690 --> 02:00.660
with what turned out to be
Danny Nasiri's blood.

02:00.660 --> 02:03.790
It had been shoved
into the back of Byron's closet

02:03.790 --> 02:05.130
under his dirty underwear.

02:05.130 --> 02:07.700
Dude, knock it off.

02:08.660 --> 02:10.699
- You think this is
some kind of joke?

02:10.699 --> 02:12.630
Stop.

02:12.640 --> 02:14.340
- How dare you?

02:17.870 --> 02:19.070
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

02:25.880 --> 02:29.920
- No! Mrs. Nasiri!
- Order!

02:34.920 --> 02:39.360
- Byron Welch, a sophomore
lacrosse player over at CCU,

02:39.360 --> 02:41.130
brutalized
a physics grad student

02:41.130 --> 02:42.800
named Danny Nasiri.

02:42.800 --> 02:44.370
He left him to die
in an abandoned building

02:44.370 --> 02:45.700
on south Kimbark.

02:45.700 --> 02:47.740
- Jealousy, money, or revenge?

02:47.740 --> 02:49.000
- Danny was Muslim.

02:49.010 --> 02:50.370
- Ah.

02:50.370 --> 02:52.670
- Byron must have wiped
the tire iron.

02:52.680 --> 02:54.080
There were no prints on it.

02:54.080 --> 02:56.910
But we did find traces
of Danny's blood.

02:56.910 --> 02:58.980
Oh, it gets better.

02:58.980 --> 03:01.120
This wasn't Byron's
only run-in with Danny.

03:01.120 --> 03:03.350
Six weeks ago, he left
Danny with a bloody nose,

03:03.350 --> 03:05.820
black eyes, and broken ribs.

03:05.820 --> 03:07.150
Danny reported it
to campus police,

03:07.160 --> 03:09.190
but for some reason
withdrew the complaint.

03:09.190 --> 03:11.060
- Aside from that, any motive?

03:11.060 --> 03:13.360
- Cpd checked both
their computers, phone records,

03:13.360 --> 03:14.660
and class schedules.

03:14.660 --> 03:16.100
There wasn't
any obvious connection.

03:16.100 --> 03:18.370
What can I say?
It looks like a garden-variety

03:18.370 --> 03:19.700
hate crime to me,

03:19.700 --> 03:23.370
but stone wants us
to dot all the is.

03:23.370 --> 03:27.710
- Last time I was
at a frat house...

03:27.710 --> 03:29.780
Never mind.

03:29.780 --> 03:33.710
- Come on. You know
you're gonna tell me eventually.

03:33.720 --> 03:36.720
- You do know there's free porn
on the Internet now.

03:36.720 --> 03:39.790
- Whoa, Nagel, I didn't
say anything about porn.

03:39.790 --> 03:41.120
- Mm-hmm.

03:44.060 --> 03:46.160
Oh, stale beer
and something nasty.

03:46.160 --> 03:48.730
That's called hormones.

03:48.730 --> 03:51.200
We're investigators from
the state attorney's office.

03:51.200 --> 03:53.870
- What's that?
Like, better than cops?

03:53.870 --> 03:54.900
- It's, like, different.

03:54.900 --> 03:59.010
- Look, there's no way he killed
that guy. He's a good dude.

03:59.010 --> 04:00.880
- As in he's a good
beer pong partner?

04:00.880 --> 04:04.250
- All right, so, what was
his problem with Danny Nasiri?

04:04.250 --> 04:06.850
- Yeah, why don't we all
just get along? Uh...

04:06.850 --> 04:09.980
- Are you saying Byron
didn't like Muslims?

04:09.990 --> 04:11.250
- You know what the school does

04:11.250 --> 04:13.120
for the towel heads.
- Not now.

04:13.120 --> 04:16.890
I mean, they're part of
the soon-to-be white minority.

04:16.890 --> 04:18.130
- Take another look, pal.

04:18.130 --> 04:20.029
- All Joey's trying to say is

04:20.029 --> 04:21.930
that the school bends over
backwards

04:21.930 --> 04:23.130
for a small group of students...

04:23.130 --> 04:24.870
- they play the damn
call to prayer.

04:24.870 --> 04:29.100
It's like... who's not aware
of Muslims, you know?

04:29.110 --> 04:31.170
- Damn it, Joey.
- So Byron was just

04:31.170 --> 04:32.870
doing the majority a favor?

04:32.880 --> 04:34.710
- Byron didn't even
know the guy.

04:34.710 --> 04:37.980
Look, his brother
was killed in Kabul.

04:37.980 --> 04:39.910
When he beat up Danny,
he was drunk,

04:39.920 --> 04:42.120
and, I don't know,
morose about Bobby.

04:42.120 --> 04:44.850
- Oh, so it could've been
any Muslim?

04:44.850 --> 04:46.720
- Yeah. Wrong time, wrong place.

04:48.720 --> 04:50.830
- Maybe we can see Byron's room.

04:53.730 --> 04:56.800
There's our motive: His brother
getting killed in Afghanistan.

04:56.800 --> 04:59.300
- Yeah, you've seen one Muslim...
- That's not what I meant.

04:59.300 --> 05:02.070
Look, I'm not saying what
those assholes said was right,

05:02.070 --> 05:04.240
but we do seem to go
out of our way

05:04.240 --> 05:06.210
to make them feel comfortable.

05:06.210 --> 05:08.510
- When I was in uniform,
me and McKay,

05:08.510 --> 05:10.980
we would drive past a mosque
every day.

05:10.980 --> 05:13.510
And every day when they saw us,
the people would scatter.

05:13.520 --> 05:17.150
One day,
McKay buys an extra coffee...

05:17.150 --> 05:20.150
He gives the extra cup
to this old dude, Ameer,

05:20.160 --> 05:23.090
before he can get away.

05:23.090 --> 05:27.060
Next day, we drive by... Ameer's
there with a box of donuts.

05:27.060 --> 05:30.970
The day after that,
Ameer brings his wife, Fadi,

05:30.970 --> 05:33.100
and his cousin Saad.

05:33.100 --> 05:35.000
- Donut diplomacy.

05:37.870 --> 05:40.940
Why does Byron have a Koran?

05:40.940 --> 05:42.810
- Maybe he wants
to get to know the enemy.

05:42.810 --> 05:47.250
- "From Addie."
Who is Addie?

05:49.050 --> 05:50.050
You knew Danny?

05:50.050 --> 05:51.890
- He was a good friend.

05:51.890 --> 05:54.020
Actually, I'm the one
who convinced him

05:54.020 --> 05:56.020
to drop his complaint
against Byron.

05:56.030 --> 05:57.790
- Why would you do that?

05:57.790 --> 05:58.990
- Just doing my part in showing

05:59.000 --> 06:01.860
that Islam is a religion
of peace.

06:01.860 --> 06:04.330
Um, I'm a member of
come together.

06:04.330 --> 06:07.000
We promote understanding
between Muslims

06:07.000 --> 06:09.140
and students of other religions.

06:09.140 --> 06:12.170
Byron felt really bad
after he beat up Danny.

06:12.180 --> 06:15.010
He came to a meeting.
That's when I met him.

06:15.010 --> 06:17.140
- And you gave him the Koran?
- I wanted him to see

06:17.150 --> 06:20.380
there's nothing in there
about blowing up westerners.

06:23.050 --> 06:27.320
The truth is I'm sure
Byron didn't kill Danny.

06:27.320 --> 06:29.160
- Because he read the Koran?

06:29.160 --> 06:33.360
- Because he was with me...

06:33.360 --> 06:36.300
All night.

06:36.300 --> 06:38.170
- He's about to go on trial
for murder, Addie.

06:38.170 --> 06:41.000
You didn't maybe think
to tell someone?

06:41.000 --> 06:45.310
- I wanted to, but...

06:45.310 --> 06:47.910
My dad...

06:47.910 --> 06:50.410
He doesn't know
about me and Byron.

06:50.410 --> 06:53.080
- He wouldn't approve?

06:53.080 --> 06:55.420
- My real name is Adara.

06:55.420 --> 06:58.090
It means "virgin."

06:58.090 --> 06:59.990
If he found out...

07:03.330 --> 07:06.190
Byron was only thinking of me.

07:06.200 --> 07:08.330
He made me promise
to keep my mouth shut

07:08.330 --> 07:12.070
unless things turned
really bad for him.

07:12.070 --> 07:14.130
- They have.

07:16.400 --> 07:18.870
- Is there anything else, Addie?

07:30.990 --> 07:33.290
- We made it
the night Danny was killed.

07:48.200 --> 07:52.570
- Proves Byron didn't hate
all Muslims.

07:52.580 --> 07:55.140
It's time stamped 12:30 A.M.
the night Danny was killed.

07:55.140 --> 07:56.380
Before that, he was
with his buddies

07:56.380 --> 07:57.680
from about 9:30 to 11:00.

07:57.680 --> 07:59.680
- And that still leaves a gap
in the timeline.

07:59.680 --> 08:01.380
- So, he commits
a brutal hate crime,

08:01.380 --> 08:03.480
and then makes a sex tape
with his Muslim girlfriend?

08:03.490 --> 08:05.590
- I once convicted a bookie
who cut off his client's arm

08:05.590 --> 08:07.390
and then went to
his daughter's bat Miitzvah.

08:07.390 --> 08:09.290
- That's different.
That's about money.

08:09.290 --> 08:13.130
This is about...

08:13.130 --> 08:15.600
I don't really know
what this is about.

08:15.600 --> 08:17.260
- So find out.

08:21.970 --> 08:23.670
- When I was in school,
I would have six roomies

08:23.670 --> 08:24.970
in a place like this.

08:24.970 --> 08:27.640
- Saturday nights
must have been fun.

08:31.250 --> 08:32.580
- "The Schrodinger equation."

08:32.580 --> 08:34.950
Who writes a whole book
on one equation?

08:36.580 --> 08:38.690
Same filing system I used.

08:40.289 --> 08:43.289
Check this out: It's a receipt
to a local dry cleaner.

08:43.289 --> 08:46.160
Dated three months ago,
addressed to Jafar Boustani.

08:46.160 --> 08:47.560
Maybe Danny did have a roomie.

08:47.560 --> 08:49.460
- Maybe he knows something.

08:52.600 --> 08:55.700
- Danny and I were roommates
for six years.

08:55.710 --> 08:58.340
Admissions put us together
when we were freshmen.

08:58.340 --> 09:01.180
One Muslim's got to get along
with another, right?

09:01.180 --> 09:03.180
- Did you and Danny get along?

09:03.180 --> 09:04.710
- We lived in the dorms
for four years.

09:04.710 --> 09:06.710
And then we got an apartment
off Ellis street

09:06.720 --> 09:08.480
when we started grad school.

09:08.480 --> 09:11.590
- You didn't really answer
the question.

09:11.590 --> 09:15.590
- Yes.
We were great friends.

09:15.590 --> 09:18.030
We're both studying
theoretical physics.

09:18.030 --> 09:20.460
- Like the Schrodinger equation?

09:20.460 --> 09:22.700
- Yeah.

09:22.700 --> 09:24.600
Danny never quite got the hang
of that.

09:24.600 --> 09:26.470
- So, why'd you move out?

09:26.470 --> 09:31.610
- A girl. I moved in with her.
Then we broke up.

09:31.610 --> 09:34.310
I wanted to move back in
with Danny,

09:34.310 --> 09:39.010
but he decided he liked
to live alone.

09:39.020 --> 09:41.480
Now I wish I would've insisted.

09:41.480 --> 09:44.520
- Sorry, but we have to ask:
Where were you...

09:44.520 --> 09:46.520
- the night Danny was killed?

09:46.520 --> 09:50.290
Studying. In the stacks.
Like every night.

09:51.630 --> 09:53.330
You're gonna convict Byron,
right?

09:53.330 --> 09:54.760
- You know Byron Welch?

09:54.760 --> 09:57.600
- I was there the first time
he attacked Danny.

09:57.600 --> 10:00.670
It would've been a lot worse
if I hadn't stopped it.

10:00.670 --> 10:04.540
- Your name wasn't
on the police report.

10:04.540 --> 10:06.440
- I didn't want any trouble.

10:06.440 --> 10:08.340
I mean, you don't know
what it's like on campus.

10:08.340 --> 10:10.740
I don't need enemies.

10:10.750 --> 10:12.750
- Thank you, Jafar.

10:12.750 --> 10:15.720
- Of course.
Anything I can do to help.

10:17.650 --> 10:21.690
- Hey. Your old girlfriend...
What was her name?

10:21.690 --> 10:23.590
- Melanie Burke.

10:26.660 --> 10:28.430
- Have a nice day.
- Yeah.

10:29.830 --> 10:32.070
- You don't believe him?
- No.

10:32.070 --> 10:33.770
There's no way that guy stops
a lacrosse player

10:33.770 --> 10:35.600
like Byron Welch.

10:37.510 --> 10:39.810
- Jafar and I lived together
for maybe a month.

10:39.810 --> 10:41.410
He wasn't a bad guy.

10:41.410 --> 10:43.310
- Not exactly a rave review.

10:43.310 --> 10:46.080
- What do you want me to say?
It didn't last.

10:46.080 --> 10:47.750
- We'd like to know why.

10:47.750 --> 10:50.820
- Why? Jafar was handsome
and he treated me okay,

10:50.820 --> 10:53.650
but... I don't know
the exact word for it...

10:53.660 --> 10:55.620
Insecure, maybe.

10:55.620 --> 10:57.520
Maybe paranoid.

10:57.530 --> 10:59.660
He always felt like the outsider
of the group, you know?

10:59.660 --> 11:01.560
Like everyone hated him.

11:01.560 --> 11:03.460
- Yeah. We met a couple of guys
like that.

11:03.470 --> 11:07.570
- So, you didn't like
the guilt by association?

11:07.570 --> 11:10.370
- I'm dating a guy
from Egypt now.

11:10.370 --> 11:12.110
- Did Jafar ever mention
Danny Nasiri?

11:12.110 --> 11:13.770
- Does all the time count?

11:13.780 --> 11:16.580
He was convinced that Danny was
plagiarizing his research...

11:16.580 --> 11:19.850
Some science stuff
nobody cares about.

11:19.850 --> 11:21.850
Anyway, he said
that if Danny did it again,

11:21.850 --> 11:23.720
he'd hurt him bad.

11:23.720 --> 11:26.350
- You do know
that Danny was murdered?

11:26.360 --> 11:27.650
- Yeah, sure.
- And you never thought.

11:27.660 --> 11:31.390
- What, and be labeled
an Islamaphobe?

11:31.390 --> 11:33.130
Look, I got to get to class.

11:33.130 --> 11:34.760
- Yeah. Thanks.

11:36.660 --> 11:38.670
A fight
between a couple of eggheads?

11:38.670 --> 11:40.770
- As good a motive as any.

11:43.610 --> 11:44.910
- That's your guy Jafar leaving
his building

11:44.910 --> 11:48.410
at 7:37 on the night
Danny was murdered.

11:48.410 --> 11:50.580
He doesn't return until 12:24.

11:53.680 --> 11:56.680
- Put 'em side by side, Ty.

11:56.690 --> 11:58.390
I never took
theoretical physics,

11:58.390 --> 12:00.620
but I doubt it requires
a complete change of clothes.

12:00.620 --> 12:03.190
- But whacking someone
with a tire iron might.

12:03.190 --> 12:06.460
- Damn. Ty, zoom in.

12:06.460 --> 12:08.660
Lower.

12:08.660 --> 12:12.200
The flu game. Jafar changed
everything but his shoes.

12:12.200 --> 12:14.770
- Doesn't prove anything.

12:14.770 --> 12:16.400
Thanks, Ty.

12:17.940 --> 12:20.370
All right, are you kidding me?

12:20.380 --> 12:21.510
- Don't look at me.

12:21.510 --> 12:23.580
You guys eliminated plagiarism
as a motive.

12:23.580 --> 12:25.210
- Yeah, Jafar lied to us.

12:25.210 --> 12:27.580
- And Danny's blood is
on Byron's sweatshirt.

12:27.580 --> 12:30.220
In a case against Jafar,
that is reasonable doubt.

12:30.220 --> 12:31.920
- That blood could've come
from their first fight.

12:31.920 --> 12:33.790
- No way to prove it either way.

12:33.790 --> 12:35.560
I'm not trying
to be difficult here,

12:35.560 --> 12:37.620
but we'll need more
if we're gonna try...

12:37.630 --> 12:40.190
- because Jafar's Muslim?

12:40.200 --> 12:44.630
- Because we already indicted
someone else.

12:44.630 --> 12:46.570
You didn't happen
to find Danny's phone

12:46.570 --> 12:47.670
in his apartment, did you?

12:47.670 --> 12:49.600
It wasn't logged into evidence.

12:49.610 --> 12:50.900
I mean, there might be something
on his phone

12:50.910 --> 12:52.470
that's not on his computer.

12:52.470 --> 12:54.470
- He probably dropped it
when he was attacked,

12:54.480 --> 12:56.210
and we don't know
where that was.

12:57.680 --> 13:00.410
- Find my phone.
- Okay?

13:00.420 --> 13:01.720
- That's the thing
on the computer that tells you

13:01.720 --> 13:04.590
where your phone is.

13:04.590 --> 13:08.460
- Ty? We still have Danny's
computer, don't we?

13:08.460 --> 13:09.990
- Yeah.

13:20.740 --> 13:22.470
- It should be right here.

13:22.470 --> 13:27.740
- Let me see that.

13:27.740 --> 13:30.710
He's right.
We should be standing on it.

13:30.710 --> 13:32.610
- Maybe we are.

13:37.590 --> 13:38.850
Bingo.

13:38.850 --> 13:40.790
- Now all we have to do is
get it.

13:45.830 --> 13:49.800
- That is why
everybody loves a fireman.

13:51.500 --> 13:54.030
- It's dead.
- Yeah, not my department.

13:54.040 --> 13:56.600
- I'll take it
to the communications lab.

13:56.610 --> 13:58.010
Let's separate and canvass.

13:58.010 --> 13:59.770
Somebody might have seen
something.

13:59.780 --> 14:02.280
- Sorry.
- Maybe you heard something

14:02.280 --> 14:05.550
outside.
- Look, I'm sorry.

14:07.520 --> 14:09.020
- Hey, guys,

14:09.020 --> 14:10.950
have you ever seen this man?

14:12.520 --> 14:14.590
- No.

14:14.590 --> 14:17.020
- I heard people shouting,
so I looked out this window,

14:17.030 --> 14:20.490
and there were two boys
fighting.

14:20.500 --> 14:24.560
- Was this one of them?
- Yes. He's handsome.

14:24.570 --> 14:26.630
- You're sure?
It was dark.

14:26.640 --> 14:28.600
- And right under
the street light.

14:28.600 --> 14:31.070
It's so bright
it keeps me up at night.

14:31.070 --> 14:33.940
- Was this the other boy?

14:33.940 --> 14:35.940
- No. I think he was Muslim too.

14:35.940 --> 14:37.080
- So, you got a good look
at him?

14:37.080 --> 14:39.310
- Yes. He was shorter, thinner.

14:39.320 --> 14:40.950
He was wearing a red t-shirt.

14:40.950 --> 14:42.920
He had his hands
around the other one's throat,

14:42.920 --> 14:44.990
shoved him into a car,
and drove off.

14:47.920 --> 14:50.020
Yes. That's him.

14:51.930 --> 14:53.590
- Antiquarks have the same mass
and spin

14:53.600 --> 14:55.900
as their respective quarks.
Excuse me.

14:55.900 --> 14:57.800
- This will just take a minute.

15:01.900 --> 15:04.370
- Stop! Police!

15:05.370 --> 15:06.610
- Hey!

15:08.380 --> 15:10.940
- Jafar!

15:10.950 --> 15:13.910
