30:33.770 --> 30:36.700
I am not a criminal.

30:36.700 --> 30:38.800
- Thank you, Jafar.

30:45.880 --> 30:47.850
- Now it looks like
we're prosecuting a damn hero.

30:47.850 --> 30:52.520
- I don't have videos like that
on my cell phone. Do you?

30:52.520 --> 30:55.350
- Danny Nasiri had a good life,
a loving family.

30:55.360 --> 30:57.520
I don't believe a kid like that
would self-radicalize.

30:57.530 --> 31:00.330
- Why do people from Ferguson,
Baltimore, and Milwaukee

31:00.330 --> 31:01.630
burn down
their own neighborhoods?

31:01.630 --> 31:03.360
- I honestly don't know.

31:03.360 --> 31:05.400
- And you never will.

31:05.400 --> 31:06.930
What I want to know is

31:06.930 --> 31:09.640
how Nasiri slipped
under everybody's radar.

31:09.640 --> 31:11.470
- That's the funny thing
about freedom.

31:11.470 --> 31:14.510
It gives our enemies
the freedom to destroy us.

31:17.910 --> 31:20.850
- O'Boyle said Jafar is
not interested in a deal.

31:20.850 --> 31:23.080
- Of course he did.
He suckered you

31:23.080 --> 31:25.420
into picking his damn jury
for him.

31:28.560 --> 31:31.020
- So, you're a good American?
- Yes, sir.

31:31.030 --> 31:32.590
- And a hero?
- That's right.

31:32.590 --> 31:34.590
- Correct me if I'm wrong,
but wouldn't killing Danny

31:34.600 --> 31:37.330
have been sufficient?

31:37.330 --> 31:38.630
- I don't understand.

31:38.630 --> 31:40.400
- Well, you strangled Danny
until he was dead.

31:40.400 --> 31:41.930
That's what the me testified.

31:41.940 --> 31:44.100
And then you dragged him
into an abandoned building

31:44.110 --> 31:47.040
where you beat him...
Well, no, you brutalized him.

31:47.040 --> 31:50.980
Now tell me, Mr. Boustani:
Would a hero do all that

31:50.980 --> 31:54.410
and then try to pin it
on another student?

31:54.420 --> 31:57.950
Well, the answer is no.
Withdrawn.

31:57.950 --> 31:59.950
Does Danny... does he have
a storage locker?

31:59.950 --> 32:01.890
- Not that I know of.
- Did he have a car?

32:01.890 --> 32:04.590
- No.
- Well, that's interesting,

32:04.590 --> 32:07.390
because my investigators have
been to his apartment,

32:07.400 --> 32:10.860
and they, uh, they didn't find
any... any fertilizer,

32:10.870 --> 32:13.030
any cell phones, or any timers.

32:13.030 --> 32:14.600
- I don't hear a question,
your honor.

32:14.600 --> 32:19.140
- What's the fleishman prize,
Mr. Boustani?

32:19.140 --> 32:21.670
- It's an award given out
by the physics department.

32:21.680 --> 32:23.640
- To the best student?
- Yes.

32:23.640 --> 32:25.680
- How many times
have you won it?

32:25.680 --> 32:26.910
- None.

32:26.910 --> 32:29.010
- How many times
did Danny Nasiri win it?

32:29.020 --> 32:30.650
- Four or five.

32:30.650 --> 32:32.150
- Ooh, that must have
pissed you off.

32:32.150 --> 32:35.960
You didn't kill Danny because of
his politics, did you?

32:35.960 --> 32:37.560
You killed him out of jealousy.
Isn't that right?

32:37.560 --> 32:38.960
- No.
- It's difficult, isn't it,

32:38.960 --> 32:40.930
Mr. Boustani, to work, to study,

32:40.930 --> 32:42.630
to dream
of being Albert Einstein,

32:42.630 --> 32:45.100
and then realize
it's never going to happen?

32:48.030 --> 32:49.540
- I've accepted my limitations.

32:49.540 --> 32:52.440
- Yes. But Danny Nasiri,
your friend, your roommate...

32:52.440 --> 32:53.940
He didn't have to.

32:53.940 --> 32:57.040
That would piss me off.

32:59.480 --> 33:02.580
Dan... Danny...

33:05.120 --> 33:08.550
Danny might've been
a better scientist than me.

33:08.560 --> 33:11.120
He might've done
great things someday

33:11.130 --> 33:14.960
that no one in this room
can even imagine.

33:14.960 --> 33:17.500
I admit that.

33:17.500 --> 33:21.070
But what I did, Mr. stone,

33:21.070 --> 33:23.770
when I killed him...

33:23.770 --> 33:27.470
That was the one...
Probably the only...

33:27.480 --> 33:31.080
Great thing that I will ever do.

33:55.170 --> 33:59.170
- I usually love
writing a closing argument.

33:59.170 --> 34:01.210
- Did you ever play
the "would you" game?

34:01.210 --> 34:04.240
"If you could, would you marry
your high school prom date?"

34:04.250 --> 34:06.710
"Would you have
stolen the formula for coke?"

34:06.710 --> 34:08.510
Things like that.

34:08.520 --> 34:12.489
The one sure "yes" is always,

34:12.489 --> 34:15.750
"if you met the baby Hitler,
would you have killed him?"

34:15.760 --> 34:18.560
- It sounds like you approve
of what Jafar did.

34:18.560 --> 34:20.630
- Whatever motivated Jafar,

34:20.630 --> 34:22.600
Danny may well have been
a terrorist.

34:22.600 --> 34:26.830
- Yes, but we'll never know
for sure, will we?

34:26.830 --> 34:30.199
Besides, Jafar's the one
on trial, not Danny.

34:30.199 --> 34:33.139
- Somehow I doubt a jury of
patriots will see it that way.

34:38.040 --> 34:39.580
What?

34:50.159 --> 34:52.659
- Me, I never fought in a war,

34:52.659 --> 34:56.159
but my nephew, Eddie,
he's overseas right now.

34:56.159 --> 34:59.830
Now, we keep in touch
with that Skype thing.

34:59.830 --> 35:03.240
Last month, he gets in touch
with me and he lets me know

35:03.240 --> 35:06.610
that his best buddy over
there... he stepped on an IED,

35:06.610 --> 35:11.580
and he... Blew his legs off.

35:11.580 --> 35:14.750
I started to tell him
just how sorry I was,

35:14.750 --> 35:17.120
but he cut me off.

35:17.120 --> 35:22.090
"No, no, uncle Billy,"
he says, "no.

35:22.090 --> 35:27.160
We do it so you don't have to."

35:27.160 --> 35:31.130
Now, this case,
there's no issue.

35:32.670 --> 35:35.130
He did it.

35:35.140 --> 35:40.710
Jafar... he admitted he killed
Danny Nasiri.

35:40.710 --> 35:45.210
He killed.
He killed to prevent the deaths

35:45.210 --> 35:50.820
of god knows how many
other innocent fellow citizens.

35:50.820 --> 35:53.750
Now, we all hear them tell us,

35:53.750 --> 35:57.290
"if you see something,
say something."

35:57.290 --> 36:01.330
Well, Jafar...
He saw something.

36:01.330 --> 36:05.860
But he took it one step further.

36:05.870 --> 36:07.730
He did something about it.

36:07.740 --> 36:11.640
He did it so you don't have to.

36:13.870 --> 36:15.810
So you don't have to.

36:29.790 --> 36:33.630
- When I selected this jury,
I was being a clever lawyer.

36:33.630 --> 36:36.400
Perhaps too clever by half.

36:36.400 --> 36:39.300
I selected you, ma'am,
because you went to church.

36:39.300 --> 36:43.300
And your son... he's matriculated
at Liberty university.

36:43.300 --> 36:45.670
That's Evangelical,
if I'm not mistaken.

36:45.670 --> 36:46.870
You, sir. You have a son
in the marines

36:46.870 --> 36:48.970
and a daughter in the army.

36:50.980 --> 36:54.810
I selected each one of you
for a very specific reason.

36:54.820 --> 36:57.680
You're patriots.
You believe in god.

36:57.690 --> 37:00.650
You have law enforcement
in the family.

37:00.660 --> 37:04.420
You voted
for the right politician.

37:04.430 --> 37:07.830
At the end of the day,
you're all great Americans.

37:10.800 --> 37:15.700
And I expected you to convict
Jafar Boustani

37:15.700 --> 37:19.440
because of who he is,
not because of what he did.

37:19.440 --> 37:25.810
I forgot that that's not what
great Americans do.

37:25.810 --> 37:29.180
Great Americans look to the law

37:29.180 --> 37:32.280
that binds us together
as a people.

37:32.290 --> 37:34.690
They ignore what their gut
tells them is right,

37:34.690 --> 37:38.220
choosing instead what we
as a civilized society

37:38.230 --> 37:40.730
have collectively determined is
the right thing to do.

37:40.730 --> 37:42.330
Why?

37:42.330 --> 37:47.070
Because that's the only way
a great country stays great.

37:49.470 --> 37:51.400
"Someone had to do something
about Danny Nasiri

37:51.410 --> 37:54.710
before he did something
unspeakable,"

37:54.710 --> 37:56.980
says our guts.

37:56.980 --> 37:59.810
"Someone had to murder him
in cold blood,

37:59.810 --> 38:02.010
"without a trial,
without a verdict,

38:02.020 --> 38:04.380
"without the constitutional
guarantees

38:04.390 --> 38:09.250
"that Mr. O'Boyle's nephew is
risking his life for every day.

38:09.260 --> 38:14.330
That's the right thing to do,"
says our hearts.

38:14.330 --> 38:16.830
But our heads...

38:20.270 --> 38:21.970
All I'm asking of you is
that you continue

38:21.970 --> 38:24.440
to be great Americans...

38:26.870 --> 38:29.270
Continue to be patriots,

38:29.280 --> 38:31.280
continue to fear
whatever god you worship

38:31.280 --> 38:34.050
when you discuss this case
among yourselves,

38:34.050 --> 38:36.280
and you think
of Mr. O'Boyle's nephew

38:36.280 --> 38:40.850
and his buddies
and what they're fighting for

38:40.860 --> 38:44.020
when you discuss this case,

38:44.020 --> 38:48.390
when you determine the guilt
or the innocence

38:48.400 --> 38:50.800
of Jafar Boustani.

39:24.560 --> 39:27.470
- Have you reached a verdict?
- We have.

39:40.580 --> 39:42.510
- In the
people of the state of Illinois

39:42.520 --> 39:44.120
versus Jafar Boustani,

39:44.120 --> 39:46.150
the jury finds the defendant
guilty

39:46.150 --> 39:48.820
of murder in the first degree.

40:07.470 --> 40:10.940
I had a trial tricks professor
who said,

40:10.950 --> 40:12.950
"all good trial lawyers drink,

40:12.950 --> 40:16.980
but the great ones
drink scotch."

40:16.980 --> 40:19.920
- Oh, you are a damn good
trial lawyer, Mr. O'Boyle.

40:19.920 --> 40:22.490
- That "Danny's a terrorist"
thing, you know,

40:22.490 --> 40:27.130
Would never have come up if
the Niqab lady hadn't testified.

40:27.130 --> 40:29.430
- You know what?

40:29.430 --> 40:32.400
The law should be pure,
like physics.

40:32.400 --> 40:35.530
It should be better than media
and politics.

40:35.540 --> 40:37.640
It should exist outside of race.

40:37.640 --> 40:39.540
- Well, if it's any consolation,

40:39.540 --> 40:43.080
when it comes to Muslims,
we're all a tad racist.

40:43.080 --> 40:47.180
Hell, we bend over backwards
trying to avoid confronting it.

40:47.180 --> 40:49.510
- That's a pretty broad
brushstroke.

40:49.520 --> 40:52.020
- It's our nature.

40:52.020 --> 40:55.590
Everybody wants to be tolerant.

40:55.590 --> 40:58.220
A white guy goes into a church
in Charleston,

40:58.230 --> 41:00.960
blows away a black
Bible study class.

41:00.960 --> 41:05.530
What do we do about it?
We ban the confederate flag.

41:05.530 --> 41:09.430
A Muslim murders 49 kids
at a nightclub,

41:09.440 --> 41:12.140
and we admonish each other

41:12.140 --> 41:16.940
not to blame
the entire religion.

41:16.940 --> 41:21.510
We are naturally racist.

41:21.520 --> 41:27.090
But at the same time,
we feel guilty about it.

41:27.090 --> 41:29.620
- Was Danny really a terrorist?

41:29.620 --> 41:34.090
- Well, you mean:
Do I believe my client?

41:34.090 --> 41:35.630
Well, I'm supposed to, right?

41:41.100 --> 41:43.200
- I hated physics.
